/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/the-biggest-mistake-netanyahu-has-made-since-the-hamas-war-began/0000018b-7b83-d1da-a1bb-7fbb2db60000</link><description>在一次罕见的黄金时段新闻发布会上，本杰明·内塔尼亚胡承诺回答问题，甚至是棘手的问题，但不是现在。只是在战争之后。在为政治生存而疯狂的斗争中，他每句话都精打细算，但他惯常的将责任推卸给别人的做法现在却适得其反。</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 16:30:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/the-biggest-mistake-netanyahu-has-made-since-the-hamas-war-began/0000018b-7b83-d1da-a1bb-7fbb2db60000</guid></item><item><title>北部未受威胁：黎巴嫩边境以前的“和平”被死一般的寂静所取代</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article-magazine/.premium/northern-inexposure-former-peace-on-lebanon-border-replaced-by-deathly-silence/0000018b-7b7e-d0f6-afeb-7bff425b0000</link><description>以色列北部边境紧张局势：留在边境附近的少数居民因害怕真主党而躲在家里。以色列多次战争中首次大部分人逃往南方</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 15:41:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article-magazine/.premium/northern-inexposure-former-peace-on-lebanon-border-replaced-by-deathly-silence/0000018b-7b7e-d0f6-afeb-7bff425b0000</guid></item><item><title>“不择手段”：布鲁克林数千人站在哈马斯恐怖合法化的标语后面</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/by-any-means-necessary-thousands-stand-behind-sign-legitimizing-hamas-terror/0000018b-7bea-d0f6-afeb-7bff5f4f0000</link><description>亲巴勒斯坦的纽约人呼吁“为加沙淹没布鲁克林”，让人想起“阿克萨洪水”，10 月 7 日的袭击导致 1,400 名以色列人死亡，近 230 人被囚禁</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 15:25:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/by-any-means-necessary-thousands-stand-behind-sign-legitimizing-hamas-terror/0000018b-7bea-d0f6-afeb-7bff5f4f0000</guid></item><item><title>哈马斯劫持的以色列人质可能成为地区权力博弈的棋子</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/israeli-hostages-taken-by-hamas-may-become-pawns-in-a-regional-power-play/0000018b-7b81-d51e-a3cb-7bed743f0000</link><description>由卡塔尔斡旋达成的释放人质协议的成本将会很高，但仍比真主党和伊朗参与的协议便宜</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 15:00:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/israeli-hostages-taken-by-hamas-may-become-pawns-in-a-regional-power-play/0000018b-7b81-d51e-a3cb-7bed743f0000</guid></item><item><title>我们必须驳斥关于围困加沙的谎言</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article-opinion/.premium/we-must-refute-the-lie-about-the-siege-of-gaza/0000018b-7b6d-d0f6-afeb-7bfd54110000</link><description>任何人还在谈论“围城”和“监狱”，都是故意混淆因果关系</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 14:55:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article-opinion/.premium/we-must-refute-the-lie-about-the-siege-of-gaza/0000018b-7b6d-d0f6-afeb-7bfd54110000</guid></item><item><title>著名科学家、数学家要求释放加沙哈马斯关押的儿童</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/renowned-scientists-mathematicians-demand-release-of-children-held-by-hamas-in-gaza/0000018b-7b75-d51e-a3cb-7b7d485f0000</link><description>包括图灵奖和菲尔兹奖获得者在内的数十位名人表示，“虽然我们个人对以色列-巴勒斯坦冲突有不同的看法，但我们都强烈谴责对平民的谋杀、绑架、强奸和酷刑”</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 14:25:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/renowned-scientists-mathematicians-demand-release-of-children-held-by-hamas-in-gaza/0000018b-7b75-d51e-a3cb-7b7d485f0000</guid></item><item><title>为什么识别哈马斯以色列受害者身份的竞赛比 9/11 之后更加困难</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/identifying-israeli-victims-is-more-complicated-than-the-challenge-after-9-11/0000018b-7b1b-d4a8-a3cf-ffbba2df0000</link><description>以色列法医中心争分夺秒地辨认死者身份。 “他们问我，‘他死了吗？’ “也许他只是受了伤，然后他们把他拖到了加沙？”</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 14:13:40 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/identifying-israeli-victims-is-more-complicated-than-the-challenge-after-9-11/0000018b-7b1b-d4a8-a3cf-ffbba2df0000</guid></item><item><title>“令人震惊和灾难性的”：这就是战前和现在对加沙的援助的情况</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/palestinians/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/alarming-and-catastrophic-this-is-what-aid-to-gaza-was-like-before-the-war-and-now/0000018b-6c92-db57-a7cb-ec9f86280000</link><description>自 10 月 7 日战争爆发以来，由于缺乏燃料、食品、水和药品，加沙地带面临着严峻的局势。以色列非政府组织 Gisha 的米里安·马尔穆尔 (Mirian Marmur) 解释说，“哈马斯或其他行为者犯下的暴行并不能解决问题。”免除以色列的法律义务”</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 14:13:32 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/middle-east-news/palestinians/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/alarming-and-catastrophic-this-is-what-aid-to-gaza-was-like-before-the-war-and-now/0000018b-6c92-db57-a7cb-ec9f86280000</guid></item><item><title>“特朗普是历史上最亲以色列的总统。他是个混蛋不会改变这一点”</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2023-10-29/ty-article-magazine/.premium/trumps-the-most-pro-israel-president-in-history-him-being-an-asshole-wont-change-that/0000018b-7af0-d0f6-afeb-7af5464c0000</link><description>对于本周末举行的年度共和党犹太联盟会议上的共和党犹太巨额捐助者来说，唐纳德·特朗普的记录才是最重要的。其余的——反犹太主义、对以色列敌人的赞扬——都只是说说而已，对他们来说，他仍然是城里唯一的游戏</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 13:41:22 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/2023-10-29/ty-article-magazine/.premium/trumps-the-most-pro-israel-president-in-history-him-being-an-asshole-wont-change-that/0000018b-7af0-d0f6-afeb-7af5464c0000</guid></item><item><title>巴勒斯坦卫生部称，以色列军队在西岸开火，造成五名巴勒斯坦人死亡</title><link>https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/three-palestinians-killed-by-idf-fire-in-west-bank-palestinian-health-ministry-says/0000018b-7afa-d4a8-a3cf-fefbe7c60000</link><description>周六晚上的枪击事件使三周前以色列-哈马斯战争爆发以来约旦河西岸的死亡总人数达到114人。其中六人是被以色列定居者杀害的</description><pubDate>Sun, 29 Oct 2023 13:02:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/2023-10-29/ty-article/.premium/three-palestinians-killed-by-idf-fire-in-west-bank-palestinian-health-ministry-says/0000018b-7afa-d4a8-a3cf-fefbe7c600